appreciations.label: Meredith Morton (Sarah Jessica Parker) in the Family Stone
appreciations.content: Reliable, organized, and serious, you're Meredith from the Family Stone. You've got a genuine soul, but the chaos of large Christmas gatherings might overwhelm you... Have a sip of eggnog and relax! It's Christmas after all.

appreciations.label: Iron Man from Iron Man 3
appreciations.content: Like Iron Man, you're extremely logical and intellectually curious. You like to keep to yourself, inviting the selected few to your Christmas party. Those who make your inner circle will be generously presented with savy techy goodies of your own making.

appreciations.label: Santa from Miracle on the 34th Street
appreciations.content: Dutiful, trustworthy, and empathic, you're as close as one can get to the real Santa Claus. Going the extra mile to make every child's wishes come true, you're a true embodiment of the Christmas spirit.

appreciations.label: Bridget from Bridget Jones’s Diary
appreciations.content: Like Bridget Jones, you're emotional, imaginative, and slightly unpredictable. You've got your head in the clouds and are likely to be found under the mistletoe, waiting for your Prince Charming. Christmas is about love, after all.

appreciations.label: Billy Ray Valentine (Eddie Murphy) from Trading Places
appreciations.content: Like Billy Ray Valentine from Trading Places, you're energetic, driven, and spontaneous. You've got a head for business and will seize any opportunity to succeed. With your enthusiasm and charm, you're likely to shine at any party.

appreciations.label: Elf from Elf
appreciations.content: Extremely sociable and outgoing, like Buddy the Elf, you're the life and soul of the (Christmas) party. Although irresistably charming, your spontaneous nature might throw the uptight types off balance.

appreciations.label: Belle from Beauty and the Beast
appreciations.content: Humble, open-minded, and intellectually curious, you're Belle from the Beauty and the Beast. You're likely to be found by the fireplace, reading books. Deep and empathic, you see beauty inside of any beast.

appreciations.label: Batman from Batman Returns
appreciations.content: Fighting evil Penguins in this cold, cold night, you're Batman from Batman Returns. Strong-willed, traditional, and fair, you ensure that everyone is safe and cared for during this Christmas season.

appreciations.label: Elsa from Frozen
appreciations.content: Driven and confident, like Elsa from Frozen, you're the true (ice) queen of the Christmas party. Your slightly authoritative nature and innovative disposition might not be everyone's cup of eggnog, but you 'let it go' and remain true to yourself- cold never bothered you anyway.

appreciations.label: Kevin from Home Alone
appreciations.content: Curious, logical, and creative, you're Kevin from Home Alone. You don't mind spending Christmas alone - you're too busy inventing stuff anyway. Burglars stand no chance against your traps!

appreciations.label: Scrooge from A Christmas Carol
appreciations.content: Like Scrooge, you're tough, dominant, and driven - you're in it to win it. Be careful not to let your goals overshadow the real purpose of Christmas. Sometimes it's good to put them at the back seat and enjoy the slower pace of this festive season.

appreciations.label: Mark Darcy from Bridget Jones’s Diary
appreciations.content: Fair, dutiful, and trustworthy, you're Mr Darcy from Bridget Jones's Diary. You're a true altruist caring about the 'Greater Good': you're likely to be found working for the local community or a charity, supporting their Christmas-time activities.

appreciations.label: John McClane from Die Hard (the character described as ‘never-say-die maverick spirit’)
appreciations.content: Energetic, curious, and excitement-seeking, like John McClane from Die Hard, you're not your usual Christmas hero. Constantly trying new things and seeking new challenges, Christmas with you is a roller coaster ride.

appreciations.label: Sarah (Laura Linney) from Love Actually
appreciations.content: Like Sarah from Love Actually, you're compassionate, warm, and extremely dependable. Christmas for you is about giving. You thrive taking care of others, always putting their wellbeing before yours.

appreciations.label: Rudolph the red nosed reindeer
appreciations.content: You're Rudolph the red nosed reindeer. Creative, driven, and forward-thinking, you bring traditional sleigh-hauling to a whole new level. Christmas of your making might not suit everyone, but it sure will be an exciting ride.

Like Frank Cross from Scrooged, you're calculating, controlled, and driven. While you might not be the warm and fuzzy type, a Christmas party of your making can be compared to a Swiss watch; timely and well organized.
